Drag shows made illegal. The very mention in classrooms that gay people exist outlawed forever. Trans people barred from employment, housing, or even being able to use a public restroom. Parents who seek gender-affirming health care for their kids prosecuted and jailed for child abuse. Black, brown, and Indigenous trans women dead in the back alleys of big cities. Queer nightclubs riddled with bullets and shut down.  That’s the right wing’s vision for the future of LGBTQ people in America. In Congress and statehouses around the country, Republican lawmakers are putting in overtime to legislate queer people out of existence. Every year, they’re shattering records for the number of new anti-gay or anti-trans bills proposed. We need to band together and fight this hateful bigotry, or the GOP is going to get exactly what they want. So the question is, are we going to allow them?
Apparently Freedom only applies to religion & guns. Be prepared to fight homos & allies. 🏳️‍🌈✊🏼🏳️‍⚧️

@ladragnuns do so much for the community, and they were supposed to be recognized for that at the LGBTQ+ night at the Dodgers game. That was before conservatives got outraged by their inclusion in the event. Shame on the Dodgers for removing their invitation. It’s international day against homophobia, transphobia, & biphobia. We obviously haven’t finished the fight. Skip the Dodgers game, give your money to @ladragnuns instead.

Back in my element. First beach day of the year, and it was gay AF. I went to the gay beach take over in a Long Beach. It’s an annual event that started 3 years ago, in protest, after someone burnt down the rainbow lifeguard station in an homophobic attack against the community.  This year the event was accompanied by a free pride festival in Bixby park, with 3 stages of entertainment, DJ’s, Drag shows, vendors, art installations, bounce house for the kids, and food trucks. All of this came out of someone’s homophobic attack against the community in attempt to scare, but it only caused the community to get closer, and organize this incredible event. @lb.proud ☀️🌊🏖️
